ration. The authors analyze and compare legal tools, rating their strengths and weaknesses. In-depth case studies illustrate how each instrument has been used in practice. Despite the impact of climate change, overfishing, and pollution, Protecting the Coast and Ocean convincingly demonstrates that legal tools are available to reverse species extinction and plan for a resilient ocean.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFishery law and legislationzBritish Columbia. 0aMarine resources conservationxLaw and legislationzBritish Columbia. 7aLAW / Environmental.2bisacsh1 aBissonnette, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLloyd-Smith, Georgia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aNowlan, Linda, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packagez978311143542808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311140824840uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486551740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774865517423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774865517/original  a978-3-11-127195-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-140824-8  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-143542-8  ACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packageb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles